title: Jazz singing great Al Jarreau dead at 76 - Breitbart
text:
by AFP 12 Feb 2017 0 12 Feb, 2017 12 Feb, 2017 SIGN UP FOR OUR NEWSLETTER 
Los Angeles (AFP) – Jazz singing legend Al Jarreau, who brought his music to new audiences in the pop world and through television appearances, died Sunday, his manager said. He was 76. SIGN UP FOR OUR NEWSLETTER 
The seven-time Grammy winner — a rare artist to win in jazz, pop and R&B categories — died in a Los Angeles hospital days after announcing he was retiring due to exhaustion.
